# ui-native component build

**Full workflow:** [docs/native-component-build-playbook.md](../../docs/native-component-build-playbook.md)

**Inventories:** [component-inventory.md](../../docs/component-inventory.md) · [component-interface-inventory.md](../../docs/component-interface-inventory.md) · [parity/README.md](../../docs/parity/README.md)

## Authority

| Priority | Source |
| -------- | ------ |
| 1 | `packages/ui/src/components/<Name>/*.shared.ts` + `.tsx` + `.module.css` (product API & behaviour) |
| 2 | `packages/ui-native/src/components/<Name>/interface.ts` (native-owned contract) |
| 3 | Layers `jds<name>-4` / `jds<name>` `generated/interface.ts` (Figma cross-check only) |

## Non-negotiables

- **Never** import props/state from `@oneui/ui/components/*/shared`.
- **One file:** `interface.ts` = types + `use*State` + a11y helpers (no separate `*A11y.ts`).
- **Spacing:** `tokens.spacing['4']`, `tokens.spacing['1-5']` — not `tokens.dimension.f*`, not t-shirt `M`/`5XS`.
- **Color:** static geometry in `*.styles.native.ts`; brand paint inline via `useSurfaceTokens` — no literals (`pnpm check:literals`).
- **Surface:** tinted backgrounds → `<Surface mode="…">`; no raw `View` with manual brand fills.
- **Typography:** `useTypographyTokens` + role tokens; never hard-coded font sizes/weights.
- **Button family:** reuse `src/utils/buttonStateBase.ts` for variant/appearance resolution.

## Required files per component

```
interface.ts
<Name>.native.tsx
<Name>.styles.native.ts
<Name>.showcase.native.tsx
index.ts
```

Add `docs/parity/<name>-web-native-parity.md` and update `docs/parity/README.md`.

## `interface.ts` must include

- Types copied/adapted from web `.shared.ts` (`ViewStyle`, not `CSSProperties`).
- RN: `testID`, `accessibilityHint`, and web-aligned `aria-*` where the web component has them.
- `get<Name>AccessibilityProps()` + Vitest in `*A11y.test.ts` for interactive/decorative components.

## Before finishing

```bash
pnpm --filter @oneui/ui-native typecheck
pnpm check:literals
pnpm check:parity
```

Verify in sample app on default surface and inside `<Surface mode="bold">`; smoke-test VoiceOver/TalkBack.
